jdrasil.sat.formulations

Class BaseEncoder<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • jdrasil.sat.formulations.BaseEncoder<T>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ImprovedEncoder

    public class BaseEncoder<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class produces to a given graph G=(V,E) a formula phi that is satisfiable if, and only if, G has a certain tree-width. The width can be set by adding cardinality constraints to the formula. This encoding is based on "Encoding Treewidth into SAT" by Marko Samer and Hemlut Veith and is, as far as we known, the first encoding for tree-width into SAT.

    • Method Detail

      • encodeClique

        protected void encodeClique()
        Given a fixed clique C of the graph, there is an optimal elimination order that deletes the vertices of C at last. Hence, we can hard-code the order of a (maximal) clique into the formula in order to break symmetries and to reduce the search space. This method computes a maximum clique using a SAT solver and encode it into phi.

      • encodeTwins

        protected void encodeTwins()
        For any two twin vertices, say u and v, the order in any optimal elimination is not important. Thus, we can hard code the ordering of u and v. Since a clique is also hard coded, this method has to be called after @see encodeClique() to avoide conflicts.
